formatted_address: 21 Choa Chu Kang Avenue 4 #B1-07 Lot, one, Singapore 689812
name: Scarlett Supermarket (Lot One)

reviews.text: My go-to place for my favourite 螺螄粉 (snail noodles). Happy that they are opening more outlets islandwide. However, the selection at Lot 1 is pretty small as compared to their Chinatown outlets.

Generally low prices BUT also low quality goods and products. A lot of merchandise are target specific to a certain national only.

And most of the goods are also labelled in a certain language only, which makes it difficult to shop for us non native speakers. I hope those who read carefully, understand the sentiment haha.

Such a waste of money. I bought this crackers and 4 bottle of nuts. Its all not crispy anymore . Tasted soft . Lao hong le... revommend the stall to do more frequent check on the condition of your goods; Try to sell on sales earlier ; get better source for your food.
A popular store that carry a lot of interesting food and drink items, some alcohol as well. The have a wide selection of interesting drinks,  Titbits available. Prices were quite a bargain as well
Counter auntie is rude, show attitude and even scolded us when we asked about membership. Not recommended to come here. Poor management
